WHEREAS, these programs must remain aligned with industry demand, workforce
shortages, and regional economic development priorities in order to maximize the return on
investment for the state and its taxpayers; and
WHEREAS, an evaluation of the M.J. Foster Promise Program and TOPS-Tech
would help determine participation trends, completion outcomes, workforce placement rates,
and opportunities for improvement in program delivery and coordination across state
agencies; a study and recommendations on state-funded financial aid to simplify, align,
streamline, and optimize is crucial to achieving the best return on investment for Louisiana
taxpayers.
THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
Legislature of Louisiana does hereby urge and request the Board of Regents, in coordination
with Louisiana Works, the state Department of Education, the Louisiana Community and
Technical College System, the Kathleen Babineaux Blanco Public Policy Center, and other
appropriate stakeholders, to study the effectiveness, utilization, and workforce outcomes of
the M.J. Foster Promise Program and the TOPS-Tech Award, including how they align with
other financial aid programs, and to report findings to the legislature.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that these agencies shall work collaboratively to
design the research framework, collect necessary data, and ensure data protection and data
security throughout the process.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the study shall include but need not be limited
to the following:
(1) Program participation levels and demographic trends among recipients.
(2) The types of credentials, certificates, and training programs funded through each
program.
(3) Completion and credential attainment rates for program participants.
(4) Workforce outcomes, including job placement, wage growth, and retention in
high-demand occupations.
(5) Program cost comparisons with a return on investment analysis, including
estimated state fiscal impact such as tax revenue generated by participants and comparison
of program costs to economic outcomes.
